docs.lead_paragraph: SARASOTA, Fla., Feb. 24 (UP) --Louise Suggs fired a record 67 to lead the first round of the $5,000 Sarasota women's open golf tournament today shortly before ailing Mrs. Mildred (Babe) Didrikson Zaharias announced she was withdrawing from further tournament play.

headline.main: MISS SUGGS LEADS WITH A RECORD 67; Sarasota Course Mark Set --Ailing Mrs. Zaharias Out of Tournament Play

docs.snippet: SARASOTA, Fla., Feb. 27 (AP) --Betty Jameson of San Antonio mixed spectacular chipping and steady putting to shoot a 73 today for a total of 285 in winning the 72-hole Sarasota women's open golf tournament by two strokes.

docs.snippet: British sterling staged a sharp rally in late week following the hardening of the English bank rate to 4 1/2 per cent, from 3 1/2, which had ruled but for a fortnight. The new rate is the highest since March 10, 1932.

docs.snippet: In a world torn by strife and in a hemisphere where democracy has lost many battles it is worth while to turn our eyes once more to little Uruguay, which has just passed another milestone of freedom. Five days of gay but dignified ceremonies...
docs.lead_paragraph: In a world torn by strife and in a hemisphere where democracy has lost many battles it is worth while to turn our eyes once more to little Uruguay, which has just passed another milestone of freedom. Five days of gay but dignified ceremonies attending the transfer of power to the new National Council of Government ended yesterday.

docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, March 5--Uruguay has reached a turning point in her economic way of life. She is like a child whom a generous parent--in this case Mother Nature--has taken care of. But now comes the need to go out into the world and earn a living by skill, brains and knowledge, in stern competition with others.

headline.main: URUGUAY ECONOMY IS AT CROSSROADS; Country Emerges From Old Security Into a World of Inflationary Threats
